  <Description>
	This example demonstrates how to isolate 3D objects by fitting a geometry,
    (for plane and sphere) on a point cloud and using M3dimCrop
    to include or exclude points near the fitted geometry.
    M3dmetDistance is also used to inspect spheres and show defects with
    respect to the fitted geometry.
  </Description>

